summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from the Great Northern Railway Company, a corporation, duly organized and existing under and by virtue of the laws of the State of Minnesota, and the Northern Pacific Railway Company, a corporation, duly organized and existing under and by virtue of the laws of the State of Wisconsin, dated the 29th day of April, 1911 to a certain portion of Lot Eight (8), Block Eighteen (18), D. S. Maynard's Plat of the Town (now City) of Seattle, to be used for street purposes, and providing that the City of Seattle maintain concrete walks and an iron fence along same.
